1) Getting the molecular gas database (gases 1-61)
--------------------------------------------------

Line-by-Line search

Go to
  https://hitran.org/lbl/#

1) click on ALL gases (all radiobuttons, gases 1-61
2) select isotoplogues, select all
   eg 7 for H2O, 10 for CO2 etc
3) select wavenumber
   0
   blank (no limit)
4) select output options
   .par (160 characters)
 5) Start data search
 
These files are ready after you click on the time icon after a while
wget https://hitran.org/results/6984229e.bib
wget https://hitran.org/results/6984229e.bib.html
wget https://hitran.org/output-format-readmes/readme-1.txt
wget https://hitran.org/results/6984229e.par

cp ../H2020/make_breakapart.m make_breakapartH2024.m
edit it so
  cd /umbc/xfs3/strow/asl/rta/hitran/H2024
and
  fhitranver = 'h24.by.gas';
and
  fTAPE7 = '6984229e.par'; %% H2024 downloaded from HITRAN website, Feb 5, 2026

run make_breakapartH2024.m

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%

